Pakistan to Allow Margin Buying of Stocks, National Clearing Company Says

-- B y   K h u r r u m   A n i s
-- 
2011-03-05T12:58:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-05/pakistan-to-start-share-financing-system-this-month-nccpl-says.html
Pakistan will start a share
financing system in the Karachi Stock Exchange this month,
according to the National Clearing Company of Pakistan Ltd.  Investors will be allowed to start borrowing money from
brokers or institutions to buy shares from March 14, Muhammad Lukman, the clearing companyâ€™s chief executive officer, said in
an interview.  There will be no limit on the amount investors may borrow
in the share financing system, said Haroon Askari, acting
managing director of the Karachi bourse.  Earlier today, Saeed Soomro, a spokesman for the bourse,
said the system may start March 7.  To contact the reporter on this story:
